</p>
<p>
    <i>guilt of my captive nostalgia.</i>
</p>
<br/>
<p>5. Her used ceramic mug, embellished with the elegant scratches from the morning teaspoon.</p>
<p>Or, in other words, an artifact to solidify our inability to organize a succinct mourning routine.</p>
<p>The uneven chip of the rim recalls the gap in her crescent-shaped smile.</p>
<p>So I am the curator of the archive of our human condition.</p>
